    • Method Detail

      • addTestCase

        public void addTestCase​(TestCase t)
        Overrides the method to check that the TestCase is failing before adding to the end of the ISwapList. If the TestCase is not failing, the test is not added to the list and an IAE is thrown with the message “Cannot add passing test case.”.
        Overrides:
        addTestCase in class AbstractTestPlan
        Parameters:
        t - The test case to be added
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the test is passing

      • setTestPlanName

        public void setTestPlanName​(java.lang.String testPlanName)
        Overrides the method to ensure that the parameter value matches the expected name (case insensitive). If so, the name is set to the constant value.
        Overrides:
        setTestPlanName in class AbstractTestPlan
        Parameters:
        testPlanName - Name of the test plan
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if trying to edit failing test

      • getTestCasesAsArray

        public java.lang.String[][] getTestCasesAsArray()
        Returns a 2D String array where the first column is the test case id, the second column is the test type, and the third column is the test plan name associated with the TestCase. If the test plan is null, then use empty string for the test plan name.
        Specified by:
        getTestCasesAsArray in class AbstractTestPlan
        Returns:
        a a 2D String array where the first column is the test case id, the second column is the test type, and the third column is the test plan name associated with the TestCase
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if test is failing
